## Storyforge

This project uses [Storyforge](https://github.com/benjaminsnorris/storyforge). Available skills:

- `/storyforge:forge` — Hub: status, routing, routes to other skills
- `/storyforge:elaborate` — Progressive elaboration: spine, architecture, scene map, briefs, voice, character, world
- `/storyforge:extract` — Extract structural data from existing prose into the CSV model
- `/storyforge:hone` — CSV data quality: diagnose and fix briefs, gaps, registries
- `/storyforge:revise` — Plan and execute revision passes, review results
- `/storyforge:score` — Craft scoring, weight calibration, author assessment
- `/storyforge:produce` — Book production: chapter mapping, epub/PDF generation, formatting
- `/storyforge:publish` — Publish to Bookshelf: web book, dashboard, Supabase
- `/storyforge:title` — Title and subtitle development, refinement, assessment
- `/storyforge:press-kit` — Blurbs, jacket copy, author bio, social media, marketing materials
- `/storyforge:cover` — Cover design: Claude-designed SVG artwork or AI-generated illustrations
- `/storyforge:score` — Review scores, calibrate craft weights, author scoring
- `/storyforge:visualize` — Manuscript dashboard with 10 interconnected visualizations
- `/storyforge:annotate` — Import annotations from web book export, generate revision plan
- `/storyforge:cleanup` — Project cleanup: fix structural drift, prune working files, resolve integrity issues

Scripts (via project runner — all support `--dry-run`; write/evaluate/revise also support `--interactive`):
- `./storyforge write` — Autonomous scene drafting
- `./storyforge evaluate` — Multi-agent evaluation panel
- `./storyforge revise` — Execute revision pipeline
- `./storyforge score` — Score scenes against craft principles
- `./storyforge assemble` — Assemble scenes into chapters, generate epub/PDF/HTML/web
- `./storyforge cover` — Generate typographic cover from title and genre
- `./storyforge review` — Run pipeline review on current branch, post to PR
- `./storyforge cleanup` — Fix structural drift, prune working directory, report integrity issues
- `./storyforge enrich` — Populate missing scene metadata automatically
- `./storyforge timeline` — Analyze and assign timeline days to scenes
- `./storyforge visualize` — Generate manuscript dashboard HTML

